## How the Points System Works at Infusion Play

The points-based reward system lives inside the Interactive Play rooms. These aren't passive games — they're physical and mental challenges that track your performance and turn it into a score.

Complete a challenge, earn points. Stack challenges across your session, stack your points. Redeem at the end.

Simple loop. But it changes how you play. Suddenly the laser maze isn't just about getting through it. It's about getting through it better than your friends.

### Which Activities Earn You Points

Points come from the Interactive Play rooms, which include:

Laser maze — Run, duck, jump, and dodge without triggering a beam. Your performance directly affects your score.

Spot-the-difference — Sharp eyes and fast thinking. More competitive than it sounds when you're racing someone else.

Charades — Team-based, fast-paced, and surprisingly intense. Your group's communication is what drives the score.

Each challenge tests something different. The laser maze is all body. Spot-the-difference is all focus. Charades is both. That variety is what makes the points feel earned rather than handed out.

